Having concluded their primary appeal is to caravanners, the duo spend a couple of days in models by Mazda and Volkswagen and try to get a feel for what life is like for the people they believe would buy one. Meanwhile, Richard Hammond drives a pair of exciting Lamborghinis in Italy - the ferocious Aventador Roadster and the limited-edition Sesto Elemento, which carries an eye-watering price tag of around 2million. Two cars are also put through their paces on the test track, with James in a modern re-creation of the classic Porsche 911 and Aerosmith frontman Steven Tyler in the rather less exotic Reasonably Priced Car

programme.title: The Beauty Queen and the Catfish: The Mystery Medic
programme.desc: The story of Kilmarnock nurse Adele Rennie, who pretended to be handsome, professional men to target, harass, stalk and exploit hundreds of women. When Dr David Graham starts flirting with former beauty queen Abbie Draper online, she turns sleuth and uncovers a trail of deception, crazy coincidences and stories that just don't add up

programme.title: The Beauty Queen and the Catfish: Turning Detective
programme.desc: Abbie Draper takes her findings to the police, but they are unable to do anything about it and the Catfish of Kilmarnock remains free to target more and more victims. However, Abbie cannot walk away and steps up her investigation over months that turn into years, with victims spread across the country and dating back over a decade

programme.title: The Beauty Queen and the Catfish: Convicting the Catfish
programme.desc: The victims finally have justice, but are still left urgently searching for answers. What drives someone, with a seemingly normal life to terrorise countless women from the same town? Those closest to the perpetrator, who are also trying to understand the mystery behind the repeated cycles of offending, share their thoughts

programme.title: Stacey Dooley: Inside the Convent
programme.desc: Documentary presenter Stacey Dooley is spending 10 days living with the nuns of St Hilda's Priory Order of the Holy Paraclete in Whitby. She adheres to the nuns' timetable, eating meals in silence, learning how to pray and singing in their choir. She also explores how the sisters - some of whom have been at the convent for half a century - cope with this strict way of life, which is so far removed from Stacey's chaotic everyday existence. Can living with these women, who have dedicated themselves to a very different set of priorities, give her new insights into her own life?

programme.title: Missing in Paradise: Searching for Sarm
programme.desc: Journalist Tir Dhondy investigates the disappearance of Sarm Heslop, who went missing from a luxury Caribbean charter yacht in 2021. Tire retraces Sarm's last known movements and tracks down two boat captains whose vessels were moored near the yacht she vanished from. Also, she gets to question Ryan Bane's, Sarm's boyfriend, account of what happened what happened through his lawyer David Cattie

programme.title: Missing in Paradise: Searching for Sarm
programme.desc: Tir Dhondy meets with island police and is given CCTV footage that has never been released, showing Sarm's last known movements with her boyfriend, Ryan Bane

programme.title: Missing in Paradise: Searching for Sarm
programme.desc: Tir Dhondy searches for the yacht Sarm vanished from, and tracks down Ryan Bane's ex-wife, hearing first-hand about her experiences while married to him

programme.title: The Fast and the Farmer-ish

Up first, Games Master Jimmy has devised his very own giant-sized 'Steady Hand' - who'll be cool under fire when it comes to navigating the windy wire to rack up all important points. The stakes are high when the bog run is both Forward and in reverse as precision and speed are tested to the max. Finally, a Fast and farmer-ish finale special 'Hook Me Up' game means strategic decisions have to be made - but it's all about the time on the clock at the end of the day

programme.title: The Fast and the Farmer-ish

programme.title: Press X to Continue: Virtual Reality Gaming: Is it Just a Fad?
programme.sub-title: Virtual Reality Gaming: Is it Just a Fad? Season 1, Episode 9

programme.desc: A round-up of the day's news

programme.title: SpongeBob SquarePants: Fun-Sized Friends

programme.title: SpongeBob SquarePants: Grandmum's the Word

programme.title: Deadly 60: South Africa 2
programme.desc: Steve Backshall investigates whether Nile crocodiles deserve their reputation as killers, and pits his fishing skills against those of the African sea eagle

programme.title: Top Gear
programme.desc: Jeremy Clarkson drives the Jaguar F-Type sports car on some of Britain's finest roads, while Richard Hammond jumps inside the Range Rover Sport and gives it a thorough workout off-road, on a track and in what he believes is its most natural habitat - the lanes of Cheshire. James May goes for a countryside adventure in the New Routemaster London bus brought into use in 2013, which is propelled by a turbodiesel generator and a powerful electric motor. Inspired by the machines they have tested, the trio then meet to celebrate Britain's motor industry with a grand finale in front of Buckingham Palace. Plus, former Formula One driver Mark Webber takes to the track for a lap in the Reasonably Priced Car

programme.title: Gavin & Stacey: The Christmas Announcement
programme.desc: On Christmas Eve, the Wests join the Shipmans for one of Mick's famous turkey dinners. Smithy can hardly wait to spend his first yuletide with baby Neil, but fails to realise Dave will be tagging along and playing happy families with Nessa. Meanwhile, Gavin and Stacey make an announcement that does not exactly fill their friends and relatives with joy, and Bryn has a heart-to-heart with Jason. Festive edition of the comedy from 2008, starring Mathew Horne and Joanna Page

programme.title: Things You Should Have Done: Get Therapy
programme.desc: Sitcom, starring Lucia Keskin as a dependent young woman learning to fend for herself after her parents' deaths. When the family faces another unexpected bereavement, Chi returns to her list of things you should have done, and opts to get therapy. Bridget Christie joins the cast as a tough-love grief counsellor, who adopts questionable methods in helping Chi move on

programme.title: Things You Should Have Done: Do Something Entrepreneurial
programme.desc: Dave cannot keep up with the mortgage on his single wage, and faces the very real threat of having to move in with Chi. Unable to cope with their debts, the family seek help from Ruth, who advises them to be entrepreneurial. Dave reveals he has a very rich estranged sister whom he hasn't spoken to since Brexit, but who may well be the solution to their crisis

programme.title: Things You Should Have Done: Give Back to Others
programme.sub-title: Give Back to Others Season 2, Episode 3
programme.desc: Ruth tells Chi that multiple bereavements in rapid succession is no excuse for feeling sorry for yourself. She sets her the task of comparing herself to those less fortunate by helping out at a food bank. Dave and Lucas have only 10 to their name, and settle for a dinner of bread and cress. Comedian Sarah Kendall reprises her role from series one, in an episode she co-wrote

programme.title: The Blackening
programme.desc: Seven friends go away for the weekend and end up trapped in a cabin with a killer who has a vendetta. He forces the group to play board game The Blackening, which punishes losing players. Director Tim Story's comedy horror, starring Grace Byers and Jermaine Fowler

programme.title: Waterloo Road
programme.desc: Shola notices an unexpected change in Portia and suspects she has a new crush. A surprise Ofsted inspection sees Darius bend the rules to keep ahead of the inspectors. As Stace struggles with the demands of motherhood, Noel does his best to prove his dedication and put a smile back on her face. Lovesick Freddie gushes over his new online boyfriend
